message.content: A 'Calochortus leichtlinii' is a type of flower that is native to California. It is part of the Liliaceae family and is commonly known as the Yellow Mariposa Lily. Its petals are bright yellow-orange with a central dark purple mark. The flower has three petals and three sepals, which are also yellow-orange. The stem can reach up to 2 feet tall and the leaves are grass-like in shape. 'Calochortus leichtlinii' can be found in meadows, grasslands, and oak woodlands. It is often used as an ornamental plant in gardens and can attract bees and butterflies.
